animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Name - Scarlett

Nicknames - Scar, Scar Scar, Babe, Monkey

Age - Adult

Weight - 55 lbs

Other dogs - is dog selective/reactive, slow warmer (takes time to warm up and trust)

Cats - No

Kids - Gets along with kids, but may accidentally bump into smaller children

Background - Pulled from a shelter

Crate trained - Goes in with treat, protests for the first few minutes. She is currently in her crate 7.5 to 8 hours 4 days a week next to my dogs

Leash trained - Good on leash. Working on reactivity/excitement on leash when other dogs are near

Housebroken - Yes, I manage potty breaks, she doesn't need to notify me

Eating habits - Good eater, 1.25 cups twice a day with 2 tbsp canned food (allergic to chicken). Scarlett will sit and stay until I say it is okay to eat. She has environmental allergies, so she gets 2.5 mg Prednisone each morning and 2 Benadryl a day (1 AM & 1 PM). She also gets a medicated bath once or twice a month.

Commands - Sit, stay, down, off, back, out, shake (new trick)

Car rides - LOVES the car. She is the perfect co-pilot and will either sit looking out the front window or will lay down.

Bath time - Will go in the shower, not afraid

Affectionate - Gives hugs, likes to cuddle, but is more likely to lay next to you than on top of you, loves to GET kisses, loves to give hugs & kisses, likes belly rubs

Activity level - Medium (Scarlett goes on daily walks 15-20 mins. She can easily go 2-3 miles, but she doesn't require it)

Play style - She loves to play fetch with her Kong ball, if you run around or chase her she can get overly excited and be a little rough

Bad habits - Scarlett can be dog reactive on leash when walking out & about (if you don't correct her right away she will lunge & spin in circles). She has separation anxiety and will whine for a few minutes after she goes in her crate.

Redeeming qualities - She will follow you around the house and likes to be in the same room with you, but she isn't needy. She gives hugs. Scarlett does not bark in the backyard (even when the 8-10 dogs next door are barking or being loud.

Best feature - Her beautiful face. She is treat motivated and eager to learn new commands & tricks

What Foster Mom/Dad wants you to know -

It took Scarlett a few days to settle when I first started fostering her, but she was great once she settled in. Scarlett would do best in a calm house with structure and routine. She has great eye contact when in the house and learning new tricks. She loves people and wants to be near you. Scarlett just wants to give love and get love in return.

Please consider sponsoring Scarlet with either a one-time or monthly tax-deductible donation. Your donation will help It's The Pits with day-to-day care, including food, vaccinations, flea treatment, treats and toys. Click on the Sponsor This Pet link above to make your donation today. Thank you!Complete an Adoption Application!

animal.description:
Matchmaker, matchmaker, find me a match... oh sorry for the singing... I’m LuLu! I’m an 8-9 year old girl and you name it, I’m probably mixed with it! I’m a wonderful lady, who still has quite a bit of pep in her step! I love snuggles and I will make sure you give them to me! My smile is the brightest and it’s typically plastered on my face! I am treadmill trained and while it’s not my favorite past time, it helps keep me in shape! I had some ear issues, in my previous life, that were left untreated, so my ears are permanently scarred, but my spirit isn’t! 
 My ideal home will have a fenced yard, where I can sunbathe and no other animals. They don’t understand my greatness. I love kids but older kids are best for my new adventure. Do you think you might be my match?

Adoption Fee: Lulu's adoption fee has been sponsored; she also comes with a free training session!

For an application, visit our website-
www.heavenafterhellrescue.org
Once approved to adopt, the adoption fee can be paid in cash or check.
 
Adoption includes:
 
Spay or neuter
Heartworm test
Age appropriate vaccines
Rabies
Bordetella
Age appropriate wormer
Flea Preventative
Heartworm preventative
Microchip w/registration
 
We cannot hold animals more than 7 days after we receive a deposit as we don't want them to miss out on a forever home.
Adopters are required to come to us to meet the pets. We cannot ship or transport animals.

animal.description:
Midnight is a sweet and beautiful girl who was turned in by her owner.  Midnight is a senior female around 8 years old who was a breeding machine until 5-6 months ago. She’s very polite around other dogs and is grateful for the attention she receives from volunteers. We’d love to find this sweet senior a new, safe, furever home.
Please visit http://www.coastalgsrsd.org/ to learn more about our dogs. Click on available dogs to see further descriptions. If you are interested in me, please contact us at information@coastalgsrsd.org or call (858) 779-9149. Don't forget to fill out our online application:  http://www.coastalgsrsd.org/webform/1774/adoption-application.

The minimum adoption donation ranges from $300 to $400. This amount only partially covers the cost of veterinary care, boarding fees, and other miscellaneous expenses involved in the temporary care and adoption of our dogs and is 100% tax deductible.

Prior to placement, all dogs will be spayed or neutered, receive current vaccinations, and are usually microchipped. If not, arrangements will be made on an individual basis. Special consideration may be given to those willing to adopt older dogs or dogs with physical problems.

Our adoption process begins with completing an application on-line. A phone screening will soon follow, and lastly a home visit will be conducted by our volunteers.

animal.description:
Geronimo is a loving and sweet 35 pound Boxer mix who was saved from being killed in Clayton County, GA.  He is looking for a foster or adopter in Buffalo. 
Geronimo loves attention and loves to play with the other dogs in the boarding facility where he is staying in TN.  Geronimo is crate trained, house broken, treat motivated and walks great on a leash.  He ignores the neighbors cats on the other side of the fence.  If you would like to foster or adopt Geronimo please email hamburgmutts@gmail.com.


*************************************************************************
Due to our adoption approval process and vetting policies, we are unable to adopt outside of the WNY area (within a 60 minute drive of the city of Buffalo – US only)

For the benefit of all involved, and to ensure the best match is made for our rescue dogs and your home-life, an application, home visit, vet reference check and adoption fee are required.   Once approved, a meet will be set up with the dog.  A meet is also required with any dog/cat currently in the home and the rescue dog.   All dogs currently in the home must be utd on vaccines and spayed/neutered.  Our adoptions are not “first come – first serve.”  Our decisions are based on the best situation for each individual dog.

animal.description: Olga is a beautiful, 12-year-old Bernese mountain dog/lab mix of 97lbs who came to the shelter 3 years ago from a bad situation down south. She was obviously neglected and had to fight for herself to keep up with the many dogs she was housed with. This now-overweight senior has a happy disposition: she’s always eager to go outside but will walk just a bit, then sit while you pet her as she watches the world go by: a home with a yard would be perfect for this lady! In a new house, Olga needs to be the only pet as she occasionally goes after small creatures and also takes a while to trust her person(s) 100% during which she guards her food and toys. She is house trained though. Olga has never received the human attention she craves but we know she adores to be brushed on her thick luxurious coat and to share long soulful looks with you with her big brown eyes. If you dare stop, she will offer her paw when asking for more pets. She is hoping to find a loving home where she can live out her golden years. Olga came to the shelter unspayed and due to her advanced age, she will remain that way. All her vaccinations are up to date. Please call 718-666-8097 for more information

animal.description:
Jesse-Boxer X male, ~ 5 yr. (Feb. 2020)

Jesse is a beautiful dog with a great personality.  He has been living with a family for over a year but they are no longer able to take care of him.  He is very affectionate with his people but has developed some alpha behaviors that make him feel like he is the protector of his people.  Fortunately, he is a smart boy and he is learning the rules in the foster home in a respectful manner.  He will need a family that has experience with dogs.  He needs to be able to bond with the whole family and develop trust with each person through training.  He needs consistent routine to help him know what to expect.  With time and patience, he will be the perfect pet for someone that understands the nature of the breed - loyal, smart, and fond of children.  
The first step in our process is to submit an application for review. Once approved, we will contact you to arrange a meeting at our next Meet and Greet event. Our pets are fostered in private homes and will be brought to Frederick, MD to meet approved adopters.

animal.description:
Soldier is not available for adoption - he is now a permanent foster.

Soldier has been with us over two years since January 2018, without a well-suited application and is a senior. 

His foster Mom has noticed he is getting dementia and we agree it would be unfair to move him to an adoptive home.

If you would like to donate for his ongoing care we welcome that - etransfer petrescue@hurontel.on.ca - Thank you!

Soldier was surrendered Jan 2018. Sadly the owner, had passed away the Fall of 2017 and the wife had to go to the hospital for her own care. 
Rumoured to be 6 yr old by the people rehoming them to the couple in 2017.

Vet thinks he could be older- he is guessed to be about 10 yrs.
They did need their teeth cleaned and some extracted at neuter, and were also vaccinated and dewormed 
He is microchipped

** ALL ABOUT SOLDIER **
info shared from his foster mom : 
Soldier is a sweet senior miniature poodle(14/15 lbs) that loves to be close and cuddle.
He is quiet and low energy and napping is his favorite pastime. 
He is fine with other dogs but would rather not share attention so would prefer to be the only lap dog.
He is good with all sizes- Size is not a factor. 
He basically just ignores dogs unless they try to get attention from whoever he is snuggling with and voices his displeasure. No issues with guarding food from others, not interested in toys.
Fenced yard not necessary- but is preferred for his safety.  
He is not  a dog to run off but he has some sensory deficits and can wander away or get confused.
He would need a leash for safety on walks.. 
Small kibble/soft food as many teeth have been extracted.
He came in to our care with essentially pink fur - which was likely allergies to the food and lack of proper grooming regime- he has to eat a good quality diet and is not a dog who will do well with yearly shots and monthly chemical prevention applied.
Simpler safer treatment is best. 
He can become itchy when irritated.
He also has the typical cough of a small dog who's had their throat irritated by a collar.
He does best on a harness or in his doggie stroller.

Soldier had surgery in 2018 to remove a toe that had a growth on it. He has recovered well but there is always a possibility, no matter how low, of recurrence in the future so monitoring must be ongoing.

Soldier is fine with children, but not a kids dog, not playful or interested in them at all. 

I would say older kids are best suited to time - ex. over 6 yrs to avoid any that might pester him. He is not interested in any interaction .

He did not seem interested in cats at rescue events.

The Best home - would do best in a quiet low energy adult /  retired home with lots of cuddle time. 
He is a cuddler not a player.
He needs someone that doesn't over-vet with harsh chemical and vaccines.
He needs a good quality food.
He is House-trained, not usually crated but is fine in one if needed. 
Has low exercise requirements and walks well on a leash but doesn't want to go out for walks - he is a home body.

*******************************************************

animal.description:
Looking Glass Animal Rescue is a 501c3 virtual rescue, using a network of dedicated fosters throughout the Northeast to care for our animals until adoption. You may be required to travel if approved for adoption.

MillyRock is a medium size, young pit mix looking for his furever home. He's quite handsome with his white chest and hind toes, and this tiny little strip down his face that looks like it spilled onto one side of his nose, but not the other. MillyRock is SO friendly and loving. He's enthusiastic about everything! His eyes show his special soul! We've been working with him on leash walking and practicing his basic manners and he's smart and eager to please. It's fun working with him. He adores other dogs and will play and play and play... I would suggest he go to a home without cats because he is too interested in chasing our cats, but he has gotten much better with "leave it" and redirection, so there may be potential in the future. The biggest thing for a potential adopter is understanding he will need some work and time, but ultimately is a fantastic diamond in the rough. He needs to learn that not every moment is appropriate for play time. He needs a confident leader because he's strong and needs firm direction. His ideal adopter should be aware that sometimes he will simply do best in a crate away from the action to decompress....Rocky is such a sweetheart who is just so deserving of a loving home. He's one of those dogs that will reward your efforts with a lifetime of deep, caring companionship. If you commit to this dog he will not let you down. He deserves the same.

Rocky is available for adoption through Looking Glass Animal Rescue, a 501(c)(3) non-profit animal welfare organization. Adoptions are subject to review and approval. Please complete an application at https://lgarinc.org/adoption-application/.

Please note that you must be 25 years of age to adopt and we reserve the right to refuse adoption to anyone. Please be advised that we will not approve adoptions to persons who mislead or fail to provide accurate information on this application. Incomplete applications will not be processed.
2/1/21 4:59 PM

I work on the sites everyday and keep them updated.  Be sure to add us to your contact list on email or we could be trying to email you and it could go to spam.

Buster is a handsome 4 year old Spaniel mix. He weighs approximately 35lbs. He is neutered, vaccinated, microchipped and heartworm negative.
Available for adoption in Oklahoma only.

Message from Buster's foster!

I am Busters foster mom. I was going to explain a little bit about Busters background/history and current special needs. While more than anything I want him to find his forever home for his safety and others it will need to be a just right fit.
 Buster was adopted out as a cute tiny puppy with his sister. The family sadly did Buster and his sister a huge disservice and did not socialize them at all. When the family divorced they returned Bella and Buster to rescue. Sadly both seem to have fearful tendencies due to this lack of socialization during the critical puppy stage.
 Buster loves me and after a year finally loves my mom and sisters. However when my brother comes over he is very fearful and barks and runs and hides in his kennel. I have tried introducing him to guys I work with and he is fearful Of them too.  I think if pushed hard enough he may nip due to this fear although he has never done so yet as I keep interactions with strangers controlled and limited. I have to drug him in order to take him to the vet due to his fear. At home with a single person he loves he is perfect outside the home he is a nervous wreck.
 
Buster is crate trained/ house trained to a doggy door and loving to his person. He plays with the other dogs. He is a perfect dog beyond his irrational fear of other humans.
 Buster will not be a dog some will meet for the first time and he will have a connection. He will be extremely fearful of a new person. The way I see Buster working is being dropped off at adopters house and him staying a weekend to see if he can bond. This is where distance concerns me. It would be nearly impossible for me to take him and pick up out of state due to my schedule.
  He must have a fenced yard to keep him safe.  His adoption fee is $95.00 
 We are foster based only (No shelter) you can't just drive up here and get a pet. If you are interested in a animal fill out the form, not a binding contract to adopt. This is how we get your information to the foster, most of our foster live in the Stillwater Ok. Area.  Application to meet 
                                                                                      https://form.jotform.com/200005720739042 

We do adopt out of state but we do not ship animals, If you want to adopt one of our animals, you must come to pick them up in Oklahoma.

animal.description:
Meet PAISLEY.  Below is her story and more information about her.  However, before you read, know and keep in your mind, this dog is a LOVER.  She cuddles, and will hug you.  What she wants most in life is to be with you riding, or laying next to you as a best buddy.  

She is complex for sure,  Could be a guardian, but does not display those behaviors here. 

September 8 of 2017 we received a call about two Heelers between Patton and Marble Hill Missouri, laying in a ditch together.  Drivers noticed them several days in a row.  Finally a Good Samaritan found them in their yard and called us. 

One of them had a severely broken leg, which had to be amputated and he has been adopted. 

Many things were touching about this couple's story. PAISLEY never left MERLE'S side. She was devoted to him.  Folks stepped up to help them, first being concerned about seeing them but then later when they realized Merle was injured, they called to save his life.  Then they drove the pair to the vet. 

THEN Rachel Riley, a faithful follower, a dog trainer, and a VET TECH, called us offering to foster them.  There is NO taking the prey drive out of PAISLEY.  She also likes a playmate dog but they must be submissive and like to play HARD!   

RACHEL WROTE:
"PAISLEY is a very high energy girl who would do best with lots of outside time. She gets along with other medium-large dogs and people well, but needs a home with no small animals or young children or access to chickens, ducks or rabbits. While she struggles with impulse control, she learns new tasks quickly...  ...With her high energy and prey drive, she will wander if left out unconfined so a fenced in area would be best so she can run safely.  Don't be fooled by her rambunctious nature, she is still a cuddle bug. Her favorite place to be is on the couch with you or at your feet."

In January 2021 we let Paisley out of her pen and are working on her being a house dog here. She readily crates, and great in the crate. She is alpha female in the yard. She plays HARD with the other dogs so she needs strong dogs to be with and preferably a male.  Female should NOT be an alpha but tolerant of a hard player. 

A bit hard headed, but if you are consistent and firm she listens. VERY athletic. This girl can jump.    

Mature weight is between 40-45 pounds.  

Adoption fee is $200. 

To adopt call Marilyn at 573-722-3035 from 9:30am to 9:30pm CENTRAL TIME. Please leave your telephone if you send us a request to adopt so I can contact you! (:>))

We may be able to help with transport. We ship all over the USA. 

You can help us by sharing posts of our dogs on your FB page and by email to friends. 

If you like music, check out our SAXOPHONE CD that is easy listen music that the pets will even like!  Michael Neville donated his CD to help the pets!  Go to our Website to download single songs for $.99 cents each OR download all 13 classic tunes for just $9.99. Simple, fast to do and YOU get something back when you donate to us! 

Want to purchase a hard copy fancy dancy CD (it is beautifully packaged)?  To receive a hard copy donate $20 or more and we will include shipping! 

You can listen to four sample songs at this link: 
http://www.bcstrayproject.org/support-thru-music/ 

You can also donate and get the DOWNLOAD versions at the above link!

To receive a beautiful packaged HARD COPY go to this link: 
http://www.bcstrayproject.org/make-a-donation/

Donate $20 or more then send us an email at   ace@clas.net   and tell us you would like us to ship you a CD.  GIVE US YOUR ADDRESS and telephone number in your email so we can ship and contact you if there are any questions.    

THANK YOU for your support and for shopping for a rescue pet!

animal.description:
This handsome guy was rescued from a Home Depot parking lot late one night; emaciated, filthy, burns to the pads of all four of his feet and a road burn on his hind end. But he is totally OK now!
He was placed in a great home with an active female dog about his same size - but he has decided he would prefer a home with no other pets. He CAN be dog friendly, but when there is food or treats involved, he becomes reactive. Better safe than sorry.
So NOW, we are looking for a new forever home for Homer -- hopefully with strong dog savvy male. He seems to respond better to a male presence. NO cats. He is great with people but he might be too big and clumsy for toddlers.
NOTE: He is one very cool dog - BUT... he is not the type of dog you would casually stroll down the street with or take to a dog park. He is reactive to dogs when he meets them on the street. So a home with a fenced yard and some active playtime with his owner would suit him just fine.
He's neutered, vaccinated and chipped and is a total SWEETIE PIE - about 3 years old, 60 lbs. and a real goober. Likes to lean on you -- a very friendly and gentle demeanor - He is a big goof. He needs basic training to stop him from jumping on you (or your mother!).
Adoption fee $250

Email or call if interested. info@gratefulpaws.org 954-462-8840 Thanks

Please download an application from our website: www.gratefulpaws.org
NOTE: Adoption/rehoming fees are applied towards the vet bill: exam, blood tests, vaccinations, fecal, worming, spay/neuter, dental if necessary, and a microchip. There is rarely anything left over, but if that happens, the monies get applied to the next or previous pet - who may have had to have an x-ray, be groomed or have a dental.

animal.description:
Estimated birth date: August 2015
Weight: around 75 pounds
In search of a loving, dog-savvy home with with a fenced yard. Must have the patience and understanding to take it slow and earn Cam's trust over multiple visits.

***

UPDATE 9/2019. One of the hardest parts of rescue is seeing a dog like Cam waiting month after month for his forever home. At the same time, it's amazing (in a dog-geek kind of way) to see him becoming more and more "adoptable" while he waits! We are so proud of our "Cam crew" ... a handful of volunteers who have put in all kinds of extra time to get Cam out of the shelter--to training class, on hikes, for swims, and even overnights (and over-weeks!) so that he can decompress in the quiet comforts of a home setting. 

Cam is awesome in group obedience class ... quiet and obedient with commands, close passes and approaches. He has made such progress and can easily be walked in a heel, put in a sit/stay or down/stay, and even participate in small play groups with other pups.  He is far better at calming himself and accepting new people and dogs than when he first arrived at STAF. He is still best when he can have slower intros with new people and dogs, but is perfectly manageable when paired with an assertive, savvy handler. He especially likes the female pups, and he likes them to be assertive, too! On a recent outing, he saw horses up close and he was curious but not inappropriately so. He gave a small whine when passing them which usually indicates he was open to meeting that freakishly large dog ;OP

A few of Cam's favorite things: chest and ear rubs, car rides, hikes, SWIMMING, and cheeseburgers, and will wait patiently (read: sit calmly and drool all over you) while you prepare his treat. 

We have been amazed by Cam's desire for affection and his eager obedience. He has the most adorable way of putting his paw on you and leaning in. Quite the love bug and so fun and heartening to see him gain confidence and build bonds. 

Day by day, Cam is overcoming the damage done by years of relative isolation. And to see this kind of improvement *in a shelter setting* (where dogs typically deteriorate long term) makes us crazy-excited to think about what's to come when he is finally, FINALLY united with his forever family. If you're reading this, please come SOON! (Cam says, "don't forget the cheeseburger!") 

* * * * * 

Moo-Woof!  Of course we know it’s not possible, but dang, doesn’t sweet Cameron (Cam to his buddies) almost look to be a cross between a dairy cow and a Great Dane? That might make him a "Dairydane":). Well, we actually think this gorgeous guy is a mix of Border Collie and Great Dane. 

We are so, so thankful to have Cam.  He came to STAF from a man whose new fiancee and son were both afraid of dogs.  Let’s just say once they came in the picture Cam began spending more and more time being crated or out in the garage by himself.  We also have some great and very positive feedback from someone who worked with Cam before he came to STAF who is also very relieved that Cam is at STAF. Cam has adjusted well coming to STAF and check out his beautiful beaming smile in the photo that shows him at his recent graduation from training:)  

Cam does have some fears while on leash (were never certain how our dogs were treated before coming to the shelter:() so we have found it best to have Cam meet new people outside of STAF and we will would love Cam's next home to take him to a refresher training course while getting to know him.

Cam is absolutely adorable and although he can be somewhat timid when first meeting folks and it might take some time for him to become the big goofy boy that lies just below the surface. He's the kind of dog that will love you to the moon and back. Our goal is to be sure that Cam finally finds a home that can reciprocate.

Some great feedback on Cameron after a walk with a volunteer:
"Cameron is a such a special dog. He still needs to work on his pulling on leash and sadly he has lost some confidence since coming to STAF.  But with positive base training, a little patience and a lot of love this boy will thank you forever.  Due to his fears and his size he will do best in a home without young children.  This boy loves to be outside of the shelter where he can roll in the grass and chew on some sticks.! ” 

Cam is still trying to figure out where he is and why he is here.  He has made many friends with the STAF volunteers and he makes sure to let them know how much he loves them when he lets out his high-pitched-squeaky-bark as soon as they are in his sight:).  Once you're Cam's friend you will be best friends for life.

****

Please see our homepage for visiting hours and adoption details. 

* All of our animals are spayed/neutered and current on shots.
Visit our website www.staf.org to download our application.
We do not do same-day adoptions; we ask that you return for a follow-up visit before taking an animal home.
You must be 21 years or older to adopt a dog from STAF
We require a physical fence for homes with children under the age of 11.  We also may require a physical fence for specific dogs on a case-by-case basis, depending on each dog's behavior and exercise needs.
Invisible fences - Due in part to increasing coyote activity/incidents in the area and the difficulty of predicting how a dog will respond to invisible fence training, we cannot adopt to homes with invisible fences.
We do request vet and personal references.
At this time, we are only able to consider applicants within 75 miles of Cincinnati.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Cloud, about 4 years old, is a Boxer mix rescued from a North Carolina kill shelter, emaciated and suffering from a life of neglect. She is a beautiful little petite pixie - 40 pounds of dynamite: a big personality in a small package! She's a total love bug and very affectionate with her people. She's house trained, crate trained, has great leash manners and knows basic commands. Extremely smart, Cloud learns quickly and is eager to please. A high- energy girl, she requires daily exercise and stimulation. A fenced-in yard is a must. She is very dog-selective and although she tends to do well with large dominant male dogs who offer correction and leadership, she's not a fan of other females, and has a high prey drive, so no small dogs or cats for Cloud, thank you! She must have a strong and confident leader. She is an absolute JOY, but not for a first-time dog owner or novice handler. She requires patience, direction and a family who will set her up for success and be vigilant in keeping her from bad situations. Her foster parents have worked with her on some food guarding tendencies, which result from her hungry times on the streets. Cloud's home must be exceptional because she is an exceptional girl! She is spayed and up to date on vaccines. If you would like to be the lucky one who gets to give Cloud her happy ever after, please fill out an adoption application here: http://www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org/general-application

animal.description:
Red Riley is a fun-loving, 6 1/2 year old Red Heeler boy,  with a soft, glorious red and white coat. Riley is sweet and cuddly, and stays right by our side in the park. He's great on the leash, loves walks on the trail. An absolutely sweet dog who loves everyone he's met at our shelter! Located at Animal Village NM no-kill shelter in Alamogordo, NM, New Mexico's largest no-kill shelter.

DOB: 11-1-13
Adoption fee: $225.

Pet introductions are scheduled when adoption applications are approved. See https://www.animalvillagenm.org/adoption for instructions.

HOW do I adopt a healthy pet from AnimalVillageNM?

1. Completely fill out the adoption application provided at AnimalVillageNM.org. Answer all questions, provide all documentation requested, and submit your application.

2. Submit your $25.00 application processing fee online using ‘donate’ button, identifying any pets in whom you’re interested. If your references are verifiable and excellent, we will contact you for a home visit, wherever you are in North America. 

3. You will then be invited to visit the shelter, and meet anyone you like. You will have all the time you need, with additional staff to make sure you have all of your questions answered, with no rush. You will be the only adopters at the shelter during your visit, so that you can adopt the pet you choose without competition or stress.


How can I contact AnimalVillageNM to make sure a pet is available?

Our staff is very small, and busy with the care of more than 100 pets. Unnecessary phone calls can delay a litter of puppies from receiving vaccinations, a dog from being given a walk, or cats being brushed and loved.  We PROMISE you that our lists are up to date, and that ALL pets you see are available when you see them. So we kindly ask that you do NOT contact the shelter, until your application has been approved, so that our pets have the time, care, and attention they deserve. You are welcome to message us at AnimalVillageNM.org, we try to answer questions as we have time. If you have already been approved to adopt, we will be in touch by phone, email, or text, as necessary for you to have the healthy pet meant for you!

How can I learn more about Animal Village NM?

Our No-Kill, Non-Profit, All-Breed animal shelter was founded in 2010, for dogs and cats in life-threatening situations, primarily from kill facilities. We are a 501c3, EIN# 27-4461260, and our financial information is offered 24/7 at Guidestar.org. To see all adoptable pets, learn about our pet boarding and training services, low-cost spay-neuter sister program, ‘PAW,’ Partnership for Animal Welfare, and our free pet food bank for pets in need, as well as other services offered, visit AnimalVillageNM.org. You can also message us there!

All of the shelter employees liked Joe a lot.

animal.description:
Harvey is a handsome boy pulled from a local kill shelter due to overcrowding. He's a little timid but so sweet. He's around 2 years old and 16lbs. Harvey is a tan Manchester terrier.  Heartworm negative.  He is potty trained although he is in a foster home with a doggie door.  He is very smart and learns commands quickly.  He loves being outside and chases squirrels anytime he has the opportunity.  His long legs make him run very fast and we think that combined with his intelligence would make him great in agility courses.  He is a talker when he is excited but is quiet most of the time.  Harvey loves to cuddle and anytime he gets the chance to burrow under a blanket, he goes right under.  He doesn’t do well in crates but really there is no need because he is very well behaved.  He is the absolute sweetest dog and would do well as the only dog but would cherish a brother or sister to play with as he lives with 4 foster dogs at the moment. His foster home does not have children but with children who are well behaved with pets, there should not be an issue.  Harvey is a parvo survivor and one tough cookie. He’s a great little dog and will Make the perfect companion. Harvey is utd, hw neg (tested below detectable levels) and neutered. 


All dogs have a $175 adoption fee which includes vet check, age appropriate shots (atleast 2 sets for puppies), dewormer, heartworm test (if over 6 months), rabies (if atleast 16 weeks) and spay/neuter! Puppies will be altered before adoption. All rescues and shelters practice pediatric spay and neuter. This is essential in our rescue efforts and it is a policy that we will stick by. All dogs over 8 weeks and 2 pounds will be altered before adoption. There are no exceptions to this rule on all healthy and adoptable dogs. 

Puppies/Dogs that are not available for adoption due to vetting not being complete can be reserved with an approved application and a non refundable $50 deposit. This deposit is applied to your adoption fee and the remaining $125 is due at pick up.

Wags and Whiskers is an all-volunteer rescue. We also have full-time jobs and Families. We will try to answer all questions and applications in a timely manner. Please be patient and bear with us . Do not contact Parkway Animal Hospital as they are a vet clinic and can not answer questions on behalf of Wags and Whiskers. All questions and comments must go directly through the rescue. Thank you for your understanding.

ADOPTION APPLICATION

https://form.jotform.us/70898112177159

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Sparten is such a cutie but he is still a timid little pup. He is going to need someone with a lot of patience. He, and his sister, Stella, are parvo survivors which is awesome. He will need to go into a home with another dog. He really likes to go out and play chase in the backyard with his sister. He will need a home with a yard. I don't think an apartment will work for either of them. If he can't go outside to play they will run up and down the stairs to run their energy off. He loves to give kisses and he will sit in your lap for short periods of time. We are working on socialization and we are about half way to getting potty training done. He is crate trained and know how to sit and shake hands. With proper introduction he gets along with other dogs. It is also recommended he go to a family with kids 10 years old or older. He jumps a lot and even though he is small to medium in size he can still knock you over if you are not paying attention.

Please contact
app@aarfhouston.org
for more information about this dog.

You can apply online by clicking on

Application

. Once your application is approved, we will schedule a meet and greet at one of our adoption events.

Thank you for considering a rescue!

The adoption fee includes vaccinations, Bordetella, de-worming, rabies, spay/neuter and microchip. There is a an additional $12.99 fee for Home Again for a lifetime registration of the microchip.
Puppies cannot be adopted outside of the Houston area until they are spay/neutered after they are 4 months old. It is against the law in the State of Texas for a rescue not to be sterilized so we have to make sure it gets completed and that we have record of it.
NOTE: In our bios, we provide information based on our volunteer's experience with a particular dog; such as temperament, training, and ability to get along with others.
AARF is a 501(c)3 Non Profit, all breed, no kill organization. Our group is always in need of donations in order to continue to give the needed medical care to our rescues. Adoption fees do not begin to cover all of the medical costs. Any donation , no matter how small is a big help and is greatly appreciated. Please help us to continue to help them. Thank you.

animal.description:
Bessie Joe is 2.5 years old and has been with her family since puppy hood. At the time of her adoption the couple were newlyweds. They have now started a family and Bessie Joe isn't thrilled with her role as big sister. She will be excellent with older children but not toddlers that will pull on her ears and tail. She has lived with cats and loves them. She is protective of her food so would need to be fed separately from other pups. She would be happiest as an only dog getting all the love and attention. 

Her dad was a PB Pyrenees,mom a PB Bluetick hound. Bessie is an inside only dog but when out to potty, she loves to run in the yard and bark at squirrels. Bessie has escaped her privacy fence by digging under but hasn't  tried to jump their 5ft chain link. She definitely needs a secure yard for her to play in with her family. She is a bit of a couch potato(mellow like her Pyrenees dad) so she prefers to be inside,curled up on the sofa or the end of your bed watching animal planet. 

Bessie is house trained (hits the door with her paw when it's potty time. She LOVES people and welcomes visitors. She is a big boned girl weighing in at 75lbs but she is very gentle.

Please contact me to request an adoption questionnaire. Bessie Joes family will be fostering her until we find her perfect furever home. They have written a beautiful bio for Bessie that I am happy to email to serious inquires. This sweet girl will be a wonderful addition to the right home,one that fits her needs &  personality. You will absolutely LOVE her!!!

Brody has Spina Bifida, which is when the spine is not properly formed. He is a happy dog - full of life, energy, and love. But he struggles with symptoms like incontinence and is prone to infections. The severity of symptoms of Spina Bifida can have a wide range and varies from dog to dog.

We are committed to giving Brody the best care possible, and finding him a home that can help him live his life to its full potential. His condition is manageable, but still costly. On top of his medical care, he requires several diaper changes a day to stay clean. He also needs balanced diet and daily supplements to avoid any infections. His adoption fee is $350. This includes my neuter surgery, vaccines, deworming, microchip with registration, free wellness exam, and 30 Days of Pet Insurance. To find out how you can meet me, start by completing an adoption application online at www.ruffpatchrescue.com.

animal.description:
** COURTESY POST *

Hi, my name is Goldie and I'm looking for a forever home. I know there are a lot of dogs that look like me needing responsible loving homes but I'm special! Everyone tells me I'm special so it must be true. 
I've learned to trust people and they also tell me I'm very beautiful -- that I know is true!
My family loves me and they saved me from death row at a local shelter. Before that, I wasn't treated well; no one taught me anything until I came here. I want to thank the people who saved me from the shelter because I know I'll find my special family. They promised to keep me safe and help me.
The best home for me will be without other pets. I also like older children. I'm still in training but I promise to try my best! I'm very smart and I want to please you. 
I love to play ball! It's so much fun to chase my ball through the leaves and run in my secure yard. I really like it when people tell me I'm a good dog! My trainer wants to help me in my new home, too. I think I'd like to learn agility games because I'm a high-energy dog that loves attention. If someone gave me belly rubs all day, that wouldn't bother me at all! 

Goldie is housetrained and crate trained; she walks well on a leash and is familiar with basic obedience. Goldie is spayed, current on vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. Goldie was born in 2017 and is approximately 58 pounds. She loves people!
Sometimes, a loving devoted home is not the right fit for a dog and we are sponsoring Goldie to help her family find her a new home -- a home that meets all of Goldie's needs. No other pets; no children younger than 12 years old. Large secure yard. Home visit required; adoption contribution negotiable. To learn more about Goldie, contact us at SacredPawsDogs@gmail.com

animal.description:
This boy Bumble has so much soul, you can see it in his eyes. He is the sweetest snuggle bug there ever was! His name suits him well he loves to buzz around just like the busy bees. His approximate DOB is 7/17/17. He is a big pitty mix weighing in at 80 pounds. He was rescued a few years ago from an abusive situation where he was believed to be kicked so hard his right rear leg was fractured and he had to have FHO surgery. In learning to walk again he over compensated and now has reversed pigeon toe (as you can see in the photos), we find it cute. This doesn’t slow him down at all. He runs as fast a lightning when in open free space, and loves to go on walks. Bumble was adopted and returned at no fault of his own after a few years. In this home he didn’t have to share his space with other dogs and prefers to be the only dog in the home. Bumble does well with older children, we recommend 14 years and older. Bumble is such a smart boy! He is house broke, and knows basic commands and also “wait” for his treat. Bumble HATES the crate and would do best in a home where that isn’t necessary. He LOVES to play with toys and will bring them to you when he wants to play. But his favorite thing to do it snuggle and get belly rubs from his people. Due to his abusive past Bumble needs a family that understands that he needs time to settle in and will give him time to decompress and learn that he is in a safe place. Once he trusts you he is the most loving, fun, playful, best friend you can ask for. Please fill out an application if you think Bumble would make a great addition to your family.

If you are interested in adopting one of our animals, please complete an application from our website at www.josephslegacyrescue.org 

Someone will contact you to discuss the adoption process and set up a meet and greet with the animal you are interested in.  All potential adopters will be subject to a home visit.

Puppies (under 12 months) -  $300*
Dog (12 months and older)  - $200*
Senior Dogs - $100*

All Canines are HW tested (if over 6 months old), vaccinated, dewormed, microchipped, spayed/neutered, rabies vaccine, Bordetella vaccine, are on monthly flea and heartworm prevention, and also have a current Butler County dog license.

*Joseph's Legacy reserves the right to raise or lower adoption fees on certain animals. These adjusted fees will normally be added to the individual animal's profile. If there are any concerns about the adoption fee please verify with the adoption coordinator that has contacted you.

animal.description:
***EXTENSIVE EXPERIENCE REQUIRED***

Tesla is a beautiful girl with a loving personality.  She loves most humans she meets (often afraid of new men) and will greet them with smiles and her classic "wiggle butt".  Tesla has a sweet, nurturing side to her wherein she loves to cuddle with her foster family & is a perfect "Netflix and Chill" Saturday night date. 

Tesla has been around older kids and we believe she'd do best with respectful dog savvy kids ages 13 years and older.  No small kids for Tesla. 

Tesla is a dog that requires structure and boundaries. She requires an experienced handler, specifically one that has experience handling reactive dogs.  Tesla has shown increased reactivity to other dogs while on walks with her foster dad. 

Due to her high prey/game drive, cats or other any other animals in the home are a hard no for Tesla.  She loves to chase rabbits, squirrels and chipmunks.  Tesla's rescue journey has been a long one and she's more than ready to settle into a home of her own. 

Tesla requires a home without kids and other animals. 

For more information on Tesla, or to determine if she'd be the right fit for your home, email: Beth@4pitssakerescue.com

To view Tesla's full bio, visit: www.4pitssakerescue.com

home_environment_attributes.other_animals: Chickens & rabbits - she'll chase as she has a very high prey drive.

animal.description:
Forever in Foster CareReina will be a forever foster in DRM's Program, however we would work with the right forever home for this sweet girl.

Meet Reina! This girl is just 3 years old and is handicapable!

Reina was originally rescued from a high kill shelter by an all breed rescue. It was apparent she suffered from neurological issues, but nothing could be found on x-rays of her spine. DRM then stepped in and welcomed Reina into our program to get the help needed so she can thrive!

Reina was born with a condition that caused the nerves from her back legs to brain to not map completely. Sometimes she can be a bit wobbly and sometimes she suffers from incontinence. She is on a special diet that has helped a lot with her potty issues though!

Reina's favorite activities include snuggling her humans, chewing on bones, going for walks, playdates with her friends and exploring the yard. She also LOVES to chase rabbits and squirrels! When she's tuckered out, she'll sunbathe looking out the window or hang out with her foster family.

Reina has lived with other dogs and cats - she's awesome with dogs but can be very curious about her feline friends. Reina is super smart and knows all the basic commands. Her recall is great (as long as she's not scouting for bunnies or squirrels) and she is very food motivated to learn anything else you'd like to teach her. She is a hit around the neighborhood with her sunny disposition and love of everyone she meets.

Reina would do best in a home where someone would be home with her most of the day - she loves to snuggle! She loves everyone she meets so she's not picky - she just needs someone to make her world complete. Could that be you?

This fabulous foster is a Doberman Rescue Minnesota foster dog.

Please read all adoption steps and policies carefully on our website. http://dobermanrescueminnesota.com/adoption-steps/

Qualified adopters are within the approved adoption area, and Adopter will be requested to visit this foster dog at the foster family home. Our foster families are generally located within a 250 mile radius of Minneapolis, MN.

All DRM dogs are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, health checked, microchipped, dewormed, 4DX tested, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention.

animal.description:
Clover (Buddy) is a gorgeous 3 1/2 year old Cocker Spaniel/Shi tzu mix who needs a new forever home!  He also responds to the name “Buddy”.

Clover just loves a nice long walk with a person he loves. He is a curious boy and enjoys sightseeing during his walks.

Clover attaches quickly to one person and is fearful of those he doesn't know. He has shown some protectiveness over his previous owner.  We recommend he be the only pet in the home.

Clover lights up when it's time to play!  He has a blast playing with his toys and can be protective of them as well.  A potential adopter would need to visit several times in order to win his trust and get to know him.

This pup has so much potential if given the time and patience that he needs.  An adopter would need to commit to working with a trainer as needed to help him build his confidence and learn to trust others.  Due to his special needs, we are only seeking a local adopter who lives in a single family house.  Clover will do best in an adults only home.

Clover is neutered, microchipped, heart worm free, approximately 30 pounds, and up to date on all vaccines. If you’d like to meet this handsome boy, please download our adoption application and email it to adopt@bobbicares.org to arrange a visit appointment. Kindly keep in mind that all of our adoptions are local only (Long Island, Queens, Brooklyn, Manhattan).

animal.description:
Posted 2/18/18, and pictures updated 5/10/20.  DEAF MALE RED HEELER PUPPY FOUND ON 1/19/18 IN TYLER, TX. A neighbor brought this little puppy to me on Friday, 1/19/18, at around 5:00 p.m., and said the puppy was traveling the road with an adult male dog that looked similar to the puppy, but the puppy came to him in his yard while the other dog kept going. I put some food down for him, and he ate like he was starving. I gave him the name Brody.

On Saturday, 1/20/18, I noticed that he did not stir while sleeping no matter what the noise was. I was able to get him in to the Gresham Veterinary Hospital on Tuesday, 1/23/18, to get vaccinated, and check his inner ears since he can bark. We had a Yellow Lab years ago that was born deaf, and made noises instead of barking. The puppie's ears looked good, he weighed 10.6 pounds, and was estimated to be 10 weeks old, so date of birth is around November 14, 2017.  Brody was neutered on 2/17/18, weighed 21.6 pounds, and still growing.  As of 5/10/20, he is 93 pounds.

Brody is very playful, does not like to be by himself, and will be vocal about it.  He requires a fenced yard, and another dog that can hear to guide him and play with him.  Vehicles should not be moved around him without knowing where he is, and he is not an apartment dog.  I am working on house training him, and he is doing good.  He is crate trained, and likes sleeping on a dog bed in his crate.  His fur is very soft, and he loves attention from people.

Adoption fee is $80, which includes his neuter and vaccinations.

animal.description: Layla is 4 years old. She was originally a transfer from another shelter when she was about 8 months old. Her prior history is unknown, but she has lived most of her life with us. When she first arrived at our organization she was misdiagnosed. We were told she had Wobblers and that was the reason why she walked the way she did. Upon further examination, it was determined that she had horrible knees and hips. She has undergone three knee surgeries so far and is doing great, still not a perfect gait, but pain free. When her MRI came back, it was explained that her brain wasn't fully developed so there is a delay in what she is seeing until she understands what she is looking at. So fast movements and over excitement is usually too much stimuli for her. She loves to play and sometimes too much so we watch her to make sure the other dogs are not getting annoyed, and she loves her people. But can be leary around strangers especially if they approach too fast. She will get mouthy if nervous. She is a big girl, about 80 pounds. Great with routine and structure. Overall just a huge Goober! Such a sweet personality and so much fun.

animal.description:
"Have you seen how fast Radcliff can run after that tennis ball?!"-Ella

"He is only able to bring back two tennis balls at a time; I can do more!"-Marshmallow

"Yeah, but at least he is able to find the ball each time..."-Rosco

There's no doubt about it, the kennel is buzzing with news of dog wonder, Radcliff! When he's out in the yard, he becomes a black and white blur that is unstoppable. Radcliff is smart, handsome and so excited to show all his skills to his new family. Radcliff is aptly named after the street where he was found by some Good Samaritans. His original family had left him there, and by a stroke of luck he was found. They brought Radcliff to Adopt-A-Dog in the hopes of finding him a home, and we are more than ready to do so. Everyone who has met Radcliff so far is impressed by his combination of energy and affection and is sure he will impress his forever family just as much. Radcliff has a bunch of his basic obedience down pat, and is more than able to pick up on any training set before him. He is quite energetic but having fetch be his favorite game makes it easy to tire him out (for a few hours at least!). Radcliff is a gem just waiting to be found by his new family!

For more information, please call us at (914) 273-1674 or email us at adoptions@adoptadog.org.

The first step to adopting one of our dogs is to fill out our online adoptions questionnaire located here: https://forms.gle/5heEH8S6c7zXBneD7

**NO PHONE CALLS PLEASE** ... We are so busy with rescuing and caring for animals and can't return everyone's inquiry. If you are interested in adopting this pet...You must fill out the adoption application at:
http://www.marlcares.org/adopt_app-dog.php
PLEASE READ all the following info. We do not reply to inquiries asking if the dog is still available, if it is listed here, then it is still available.

Cricket was found with Possum on a rural country road.  After asking around we found out that she had been left behind and other people had been shooting at her and we found a BB in her back.  She was happy to see us and gave us kisses immediately when we found her.  She is a happy, sweet, affectionate dog that loves other dogs and everyone she meets.  We have no idea what breed mixture she is, most likely a cattle dog mix of some sort.  She is kennel trained.  She is in a foster home with small and large dogs.  She is approx 3 years old and approx 35 lbs as of Jan 2018.

$150 adoption fee, spayed/neutered, microchipped, current vaccinations, and currently being kennel trained.

ADOPTION APPLICATION: If you are interested in this pet you must fill out the Adoption Application…which you can find on this site or you can copy and paste this link … http://www.marlcares.org/adopt_app-dog.php
This does not obligate you in any way. If this does not work for you then you can email us at midsouthpets@aol.com for one.

PLEASE DO NOT CONTACT US BEFORE READING THE FOLLOWING INFO:  
Your inquiry may not get a reply if you have not read the info we have taken the time to provide.  PLEASE READ about our ADOPTION PROCESS AND REQUIREMENTS provided on this site before contacting us.  You can find it quickly by clicking on our NAME or MORE ABOUT US in the column to the right of this pet’s description.  All your questions can be answered by reading the following info provided below.  Our pets are fostered in the Memphis Area, a tri-state area, TN/AR/MS.  Most are fostered in Red Banks, MS.  

We do not allow meetings with any of our dogs until we have your Adoption Application.  Adopting a new family member should involve a well-thought out and deliberate process. This is not an impulse purchase. Please understand that we do not want these animals to be homeless again. We try to complete the process as quickly as possible and appreciate all the applications and will consider each and every one we receive. 

Filling out the Adoption Application does not obligate you in any way, but simply tells us a little bit about you and whether you and this pet would be a good fit for each other.  We will call you after we receive your application and answer all your questions and talk to you about this pet.  After being approved, we will set up a time to bring the pet to meet you and your family and pets or set up a time for you to meet the pet at the foster home.

NO PHONE CALLS PLEASE.  Rescue is a full time job every day.  Please know because we are so very busy with the dogs along with processing applications, updating webpage’s, rescuing, in many vet appointments, caring for seniors and hospice dogs, etc, etc that we are not able to return phone calls or emails asking if this dog is still adoptable, how much is it to adopt, is it house trained etc…We have included all the info we have on this dog at this current time and update the bio as we learn more about them.  We kennel train all the dogs and will indicate if there are housebreaking issues that we have discovered.  We update our site regularly so if the dog is listed here they are in fact adoptable, but may have applications coming in on them, so if you are interested, you need to get your application in now.

**WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO REFUSE ANY ADOPTION**  Our first concern is the happiness and welfare of the animal.  We respect our potential adoptors and appreciate your interest in adopting one of our pets.  We care about you too and that you are getting the right fit for your home and lifestyle.  By following our process, together we can make sure you are getting the right pet.**

NOTE: We prefer to adopt in the Mid-South AREA, usually no more than 1-2 hours away in driving distance. It is up to the foster home, how far they are willing to drive. We rarely adopt long distance, but will consider each and every application. 
 
MidSouth Animal Rescue League is an all breed, 501c3, non-profit organization that prefer to rescue senior dogs and special cases.  WE LOVE ROTTWEILERS...With 20 years of experience with our beloved ROTTWEILER breed, and little help for this breed in our area, we try to focus on rescuing them and try not to ever have to turn any away that need us…especially the seniors that end up in shelters.  Currently, we have several senior rottweilers in our hospice foster program.  We always need more fosters so that we never have to say NO to them or other seniors.  

We have also started a community relief effort specifically in the Red Banks, MS area not far from us, called The Dog House Project, where we go door to door providing dog houses to dogs on chains and other dogs and cats without proper shelter, including straw in cold temps, as well as food and other supplies as needed.   We offer free spay/neuter services to those animals and continue to check on them all year.  To date many have been spayed and neutered and some have been surrendered from their neglected lives on chains.  We are making a difference and need your donations to continue this program.  We always need igloo type dog houses.  

MidSouth Animal Rescue League relies on the kindness, generosity, and financial support of people like you so that we can continue to rescue and care for dogs like this one. We are a group of dedicated volunteers who respond to animals in need in shelters, strays, and from individuals. We receive no federal or state funds and are supported solely by private donations. 

Many of the animals we save are in need of special medical care or surgery to bring them back to health before they can be placed. Veterinary care, vaccinations, tests, x-rays, medications, spay and neutering, heartworm prevention, flea/tick prevention, worming, food, kennels, grooming, and other supplies are provided for each dog while in our care.

animal.description:
GRACIE IS LOOKING FOR HER FOREVER HOME.

This sweet, gentle girl is an old soul. She looks into your eyes with with such patience and wisdom.

She is 9 years young and a smaller girl… around 60lbs. She is easy going and mellow but has a playful side, too.

Her owner since puppyhood could no longer keep her due to life changes, and she misses him. But Gracie is recovering her happiness in her foster home with AFLAR. She is looking for that special someone to bond with again. He was a truck driver and she used to ride with him in the truck every day. She is happy on car rides, and waits politely for her person to return from errands.

Gracie is a very special dog. She is very tuned in to people, and naturally moves to give comfort and affection when needed. She would make a wonderful therapy dog. She is gentle and calm, and loves to snuggle with her head on your lap. Her energy is very soothing and healing to be around.

Gracie is crate trained and is very comfortable in her crate. She has had some obedience training. She is really smart, learns quickly, listens to commands, and wants to please. She has lovely house manners, and doesn’t chew or get into things she’s not supposed to.

Gracie is also playful. She likes her squeaky toys and balls, and loves her walks. She lived happily with a cat, and shared her water bowl. 
 She gets along well with other dogs who are respectful of her and have a mellow, calm energy. She would prefer, however, to be your one and only, and give you all her love.

Gracie would love a home where her family is around a lot, because she doesn't like to be alone too much... and she has so much love to give!

If you are interested in a wonderful companion and someone who will love you unconditionally, GRACIE is your girl!!!

CONTACT: (805) 445-3535
info@allforloveanimalrescue.org

Sally’s Story
I was found wandering the roads with my Shepherd friend. We had been looking all over for food and couldn't find any. We hadn't had much to eat in a longtime and I was so hungry that I finally laid down in the pavilion of Overton Park about to give up. I saw this person sit down with his dogs and that dog looked so happy, he was getting plenty of water, treats, and love from his owner. I picked up my head and the man saw me and called out to me, but I got scared. I was really nervous but then he took out something that smelled so good I could not resist it. I went over and gobbled it right up. He kept producing this yummy food all the way to his house where we went inside. We were out of the heat and he fed my shepherd friend and I both our first good meal in weeks. We are hanging out here until we find our forever homes!I am crate trained, potty trained, and have even learned how to sit and stay for treats. Cats and strange dogs make me a little too excited but I am so ready to meet my forever family! Could that be you?

Behaviors not listed have yet to be tested.

animal.description:
Sparky is one of 6, 8 week old puppies that were dumped near Joliff Bridge railroad tracks.  He and his litter mates would have frozen to death had someone not contacted the Clinton County Animal Control Officer. Sparky was adopted from us and returned now 2 years old, emaciated, and having severe pain in his joints and jaw. 

He has had an extensive knee surgery, and is now recovered. Sparky has auto-mediated poly arthritis. He has good days and bad days where his joints hurt, and sometimes has trouble moving around. He will need special vet care, and medication for the remainder of his life. He has been seen at the University of Illinois by a specialist there.

Potential adopters can visit our website at www.centraliahumanesocietyil.org to find our online application. Our application consists of a vet check - adopters must take their current/past pets to the vet yearly for vaccines, and dogs must be given heartworm prevention 12 months out of the year. 

All adult dogs have been spayed/neutered, microchipped, wormed, heartworm tested, receive heartworm preventative, and are current on shots, including canine flu vaccine. Puppies are current on shots and wormed.  They will be spayed/neutered and microchipped once they become of age.

See our website for hours, fees and directions to come visit!

animal.description:
Say hi to Molena. This sweet girl is house and crate trained. She likesolder kids and some polite MALE dogs. Cats are a NO. She is people social and loves meeting new people. This is a velcro cat-like dog! She rubs on you, wraps around your legs, climbs into your lab. She is spayed, HW negative, micro chipped, and current on her vaccinations. Mo doesn't like to do her business with an audience. She will potty on leash but really prefers a fenced yard. After an adjustment period, Mo can be trusted not to chew or potty in your home.
If you are interested in offering this sweet flower a place in your heart, fill out our on-line application at www.etnpitbullrescue.org.East TN Pit Bull Rescue adopts out to companion homes only. Adoptions require an application that is verified, a meeting that includes ALL members of the household, a home visit, and a trial period. We do not place our dogs in homes with unaltered pets or homes that have pets but do not have a vet. All of our dogs are placed as inside pets, spayed/neutered, micro chipped, vaccinations current, and HW- or treated within the last 6 months for heart worms by our vet. Adoption fees start at $150 for adults and $200 for pups. If you are interested in offering this pet a responsible and loving home, please fill out the on-line application at www.etnpitbullrescue.org. East TN Pit Bull Rescue is a Tennessee Non-profit corporation with 501(c)(3) status. Your donations to sponsor pets are tax deductible. If you would like to sponsor this pet, please go to www.paypal.com and make a donation to donations@etnpitbullrescue.org OR contact Butler's Animal Clinic at 865-531-7311 to make a donation on the East TN Pit Bull Rescue Account. Please be sure to add the pets name in the comments section. Your donations are greatly needed and appreciated.

animal.description:
WE WILL BE HOLDING ADOPTIONS ON SATURDAYS & SUNDAYS FROM 10-4 PM at our Adoption Center.  No appointments necessary.   Our adoption center is located next to CAL Ranch at 232 North Jones (I-95) Suite 170.   

Jack is about   4 1/2  yrs old.   He came into a high kill shelter where we rescued him from.  He was very emaciated (only weighed 52 lbs).   He is very smart and eager to learn.  He loves to play fetch as his favorite but also will keep himself busy with other toys.  

He is strong on the Doberman gene, so when he is on a walk, he will bark and lung at strangers if they are within a couple feet radius.  (he corrects easily and listens to "no" from his owner)    People walking further away than that, he ignores.  

He is a very beautiful Dobie who needs a strong owner to give him guidance and structure and they will be amazed on what he can be.  He would do best with someone who understands the breed or a similar breed.   He needs a home with out children or teens due to his protective nature.   

He will not be placed in a home where we do not feel is a safe situation for him or the home.  More will be known about me soon.

If you are interested in Jack, please contact dogrescuelv@hotmail.com to confirm the dog you are interested in,  will be attending that particular event.  We have limited space at the store, therefore we can not take every dog out to the event.

Jack is spayed/neutered, has current vaccinations and includes a microchip, deworming and 2 free vet visits.  Adoption fee applies.  Please make sure you have read the information listed on the homepage for requirements and restrictions. 

Foster homes & volunteers are always needed.  Please contact us regarding how you can help by fostering or volunteering for our organization.

animal.description:
AMOUR WOULD LOVE TO BE IN A FOSTER HOME WHILE SHE IS WAITING TO BE ADOPTED. IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN FOSTERING AMOUR, PLEASE GO TO THE MAKE A DIFFERENCE RESCUE FACEBOOK PAGE AND SEND A PRIVATE MESSAGE THAT INCLUDES YOUR PHONE NUMBER AND EMAIL ADDRESS.


Meet beautiful Amour. She is a 7 year old Terrier mix. Amour was forced to be on the streets, no home or shelter exposed to the frigid temperatures. This little girl was on her way to being a statistic, frost bite setting in on her toes and open wounds that were swollen on her rear leg. We are thankful for the good Samaritan who took Amour in and called us. She immediately had surgery to remove two sores and was spayed. 

 Amour developed kidney failure a few months ago. Her recent lab work shows her kidney function has improved and she now only requires SQ fluids every 3-4 days. She is on special food for her kidney failure. She needs to have a quiet home without other dogs and children.  Amour is very good on a leash when going for walks. Her forever home is required to have a fenced yard where she can safely explore and play. Amour is spayed, up to date on her vaccinations, on monthly heartworm preventative as well as house and crate trained. As her name implies, she is full of love and she cannot wait to share her love with her forever family.
 

All dogs we rescue stay with us until they find their forever homes. We do not do same day adoptions. A home visit is required to ensure our dog is going to a safe environment and our dog gets along with your dog(s) and/or cat(s). We require all our dogs over the age of 1 year attend 1 obedience class (6 week session) outside the home. You must live within 1 hour of Birmingham, MI to adopt one of our dogs. No out of state or outside the U.S. adoptions or fosters.Amour's adoption fee is $275.

animal.description:
Rubirosa is a spirited girl.  She wants to play fetch any time someone comes to see her - check out her video!  She loves playing in the water, too, and plays daily with the hose when we change her water -even when it’s cold outside!  She is also toy crazy.  You could toss a ball all day for her! She'll get the ball and then drop it at your feet so you'll throw it again. Rubirosa is housetrained and crate trained. She just loves walks.

Rubirosa's best home would be with a young active female.

Rubirosa had a rough start to her life; we rescued her during an animal cruelty investigation, and we discovered she had an embedded collar. She had major surgery on her neck but she is healthy and doing well now.  However, she will require a fenced in yard so she can run around after having been chained up inhumanely. 

Rubirosa's date of birth is 9/22/2016 and she weighs about 51 pounds. She will be happy in a home with other dogs and older children. She has been in a foster home with 2 other dogs and enjoys going on walks with them in the neighborhood. 

*We did receive a donated Wisdom Panel DNA test for Rubirosa and we found out she is: 87.5% American Staffordshire Terrier and 12.5% Breed Groups: Herding & Guard.

You can submit an adoption application for this ‘fetching’ young lady at http://www.fayettefcar.com/applicationform, where you can also review FCAR’s adoption requirements.

All FCAR adoptable dogs have been spayed or neutered, are current on all vaccines, on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, microchipped, and come with a 30-day pet health guarantee. The adoption fee is $95 with an approved application. A fenced yard is required for Rubirosa.

animal.description:
Friends to the Forlorn
Adopt-a-BullCant Adopt? Apply to Foster Kali Today!Breed: Pit Bull Gender: Female Estimated Date of Birth: May 23, 2012 Size: 50lbs Location: Dallas, GA
RESCUING KALI
In June 2012, 3 puppies were dumped at Animal Control. They were only a few days old and without a mom so their chances of survival were slim. The next day, Animal Control brought in a lactating female. Although she may or may not have been the real mom, she stepped up to the challenge. The mom and AC Staff did everything they could, but 2 pups died.
The wonderful people at Animal Control reached out to us and agreed to hold the mom and the surviving female puppy for a few weeks until we could pick them up. The mom was treated for heartworms. The puppy,Kali, was a healthy girl.
ABOUT KALI
Kali has a zest for life and she loves toys! She'll zoom around with any toy you give her. She is completely happy to run around with a ball in her mouth all afternoon. Kali is a bundle of fun-loving energy that would enjoy any activity as long as she is with her people. She would be a fantastic running or hiking partner. She would even just be happy to chase the ball around the yard for you. Seriously, this girl could play fetch for days. Playing fetch with a Chuck-It would be a dream for her. Kali has done well with other submissive male dogs that can handle her energy. Kali would do best in a home with older children, 13 and up. Her best friend, Teddy, and her mother have both been adopted and Kali is patiently waiting for her fun-loving family to arrive. This girl is full of vigor, smiles, and personality! She would prefer to be the only dog in the home, but with proper introductions and the right canine match she would likely be okay with a canine companion.
Photo Album of Kali: https://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.531860010205503.1073741859.162554320469409&type=1&l=eff6e419eb
Our adoption fee is $300. All dogs are current on vaccinations, spayed or neutered, micro-chipped, on heartworm prevention, and are fed top of the line grain-free food.www.savingpitbulls.org

Please fill out an application and let's get you all matched up with a loving new "furever' companion and friend. You'll find the application on the "Available Dogs" page.

NOTE:

Adoptions to Central/South Texas residents only

Standard Adoption Fee Adult Dog: $250 ea. Puppy Adoption Fee: $300 ea. Reduced rates for Seniors dogs (10 and up). Reduced rates for pairs (when adopted together). All adoption fees are subject to sales tax per the State of Texas. DDRTX only adopts in Central/South Texas.

Email: ddrtxinfo@gmail.com Primary Website: www.DDRTX.org
Mr. Louie Luckenbach is a big boy at almost 35 pounds. Louie has suffered a lifetime of abuse and neglect and while he is very sweet and loving, he can be unpredictable and would need an experienced home. He is very sensitive about his amputated toe even though it has healed; it caused him a great deal of pain for possibly a very long time. He has some permanent hair loss due to food allergies. He is food aggressive but his foster mom is working with him on it. He is perfectly house trained.
Love dachshunds and not ready to adopt or circumstances won't permit having a dog? How about being a sponsor or making a donation. Every one of our dachshunds receives excellent medical care along with day to day food, love and housing. Being non-profit, we rely on generous individuals like yourselves to help save these fur babies. You can do this specifically for one dog with the sponsor button on their webpage or a general donation on our "How To Help" page. Easy and quick through Pay Pal or your debit/credit card. You generosity is sincerely appreciated by all and is tax deductable. Need other ideas? You'll find tons of them on the How to Help tab. All contributions are tax deductable.

Diamond Dachshund Rescue of Texas is a non-profit 501(c)(3) volunteer organization with focus on rescue and adoption of pure breed Dachshunds. All dogs are fully vetted and housed on private property. Meetings are scheduled upon adoption approval. Thank you for your continued support to the rescue and shelter communities!

animal.description:
Reggie is a gorgeous 6 year old male Labrador Retriever/Pit Bull Terrier mix. He weighs about 55 pounds - just the right size for lots of fun and lots of cuddling too! Reggie is a super friendly guy and he likes to have a good time, but he also enjoys lounging around.  This handsome fellow does guard his food, so he needs an owner who understands his boundaries.  Due to this, he must go to a home with no kids under the age of 12.  He also needs to be your only furry companion - he kindly requests a household with no other dogs or cats.  Reggie is a sweet boy and he deserves a wonderful and loving home.  He's been patiently waiting for that perfect match.

His minimum adoption fee is $95 plus a $12 fee for rabies registration for McLean County residents. 

He has been neutered, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.

For information about this dog's breed(s), visit: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/abc.htm

animal.description:
Stu is a big, goofy dog who is loving and fun!  He loves to go on walks and does very well with his harness and leash.  He is a solid (BIG) dog and would probably knocks smaller children over by accident  so older children might be a better fit for him.

He is very smart and trains easily, especially if he knows there is a treat involved.  He loves to show you how intelligent he is.  He knows sit, wait and okay(release).  Stu loves to play with balls, ropes and he loves peanut butter!

Stu is a cuddler and loves to sleep in bed with you if allowed but is just as happy in a big fluffy dog bed.   He likes to walk and does well with a leash and harness.  He is a very chill dog and you will fall in love with him instantly.

He is house broken and crate trained.  He takes medication for separation anxiety.  He is not a big barker, but will let you know when there is someone around the house is he not accustomed to be it two or four legged.


To learn more contact us at adoption@ihadro.org or apply today at www.ihadro.org!  Thank you for your interest.

home_environment_attributes.other_animals: Stu does better with female dogs, he is dog particular.  No cats or small dogs.  Kids are ok but he is very strong and so it would be best if they had some dog experience.

animal.description:
We do not know Stoney's racing name.  His tattoos are unclear,  We have determined that he was born in February 2009, but that's all we know about him.

Stoney was found by a Good Samaritan on Gladstone Street in League City.  He was emaciated, covered in fleas and had intestinal parasites.  He was anemic and was in generally terrible condition.  The League City Animal Control release him to us so we could nurse him back to health.

We are happy to report that Stoney has gained alot of weight, he is free of the blood-sucking parasites, and his bloodwork has improved.  He is out of the woods medically speaking, so now we are looking for a special family that will open their hearts and their home and keep him safe for the rest of his life.

His personality is very sweet and he loves people and snuggling.  He is sweet with small dogs at PetSmart and we believe he will be good with cats, although we have not yet cat tested him.  Stoney knows how to do stairs. He currently weighs 60lbs.

Stoney did not do well as an only dog in an apartment all day long by himself. He thrives in a home with a dog door. We are currently adjusting his meds and with any luck he should be available again soon.

01/12/2019. PUPDATE!!!  Due to his ongoing medical issues it has been decided that Stoney will be kept by FastK9’s in Permanent Foster status. Any donations toward his ongoing medical treatment would be greatly appreciated. 

Stoney is no longer Available for Adoption.
